      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VANDEVELDE (1) has been plying his trade in much harder Group races of late and will appreciate the sharp drop back in company here. Has placed around this circuit and maps ideally for this contest from gate two. Goes on top. PINK VIXEN (3) didn't measure up in G3 grade at the latest effort but the form prior was full of merit. Worth another chance with the 2kg claim. ARGENTUM ROCK (4) has a win and a second from two attempts over this track and trip and should get a cosy run in transit from the inside marble. Top-three aspirations. ZOUSAIN GIRL (9) got a confidence building victory at Toowoomba last start and winning rider Zechner sticks in the irons. In the mix. UNIQUELY FAMOUS (6) next best from the champion Waller yard.",
